To avoid having `&gt;&gt;` eliminate whitespace from your input, the easiest change is simply to use `is.get(c)` instead of `is &gt;&gt; c`. [std::basic_istream&lt;CharT,Traits&gt;::get](https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/io/basic_istream/get) behaves as an *Unformatted* input function and will provide a character-by-character read of everything in the file. The [std::basic_iostream](https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/io/basic_iostream) operator `&gt;&gt;` provides for *Formatted* input which eliminates whitespace.

Changing to istream.`get()` provides the behavior you describe,


